            , I am a hair-dresser, and live in Shoreditch. On the 7th of March the prisoner came, and offered me two new hair-fronts for sale; he asked 3s. for them - I said he had not asked a quarter of the value - I said I thought he had stolen them - I sent for an officer, and gave him in charge - he had three examinations, and was then discharged.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM EDGE. I am a <rs id="t18270405-110-viclabel616" type="occupation">hair-dresser</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-110-victim713 t18270405-110-viclabel616"></join>, and live in Aldersgate-street. I lost two hair-fronts from my counter on the 6th of March - I know these; they are my work, and are worth 30s. the lowest price; I lost five or six others on the same day.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I bought them of a Jew for half-a-crown - I then took them to this gentleman to sell, and he detained me.</p>
